1
00:00:20.020 --> 00:00:22.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So, what do you think
of the O’Briens’ plan

2
00:00:22.689 --> 00:00:24.858 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to name their baby Sean?

3
00:00:26.067 --> 00:00:29.362 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, I kind of like it.
Sean… has a nice ring to it.

4
00:00:29.446 --> 00:00:33.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Except that in Bajoran
<i>Sean </i>means "swamp."

5
00:00:33.116 --> 00:00:34.784 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do the O’Briens know that?

6
00:00:34.868 --> 00:00:36.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I doubt it.

7
00:00:36.369 --> 00:00:37.912 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Someone should tell them.

8
00:00:37.996 --> 00:00:39.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I nominate you.

9
00:00:40.582 --> 00:00:42.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
DAX: Morning.

10
00:00:46.212 --> 00:00:47.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Neck bothering you again?

11
00:00:47.881 --> 00:00:51.301 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s… it’s just a muscle pull.

12
00:00:51.384 --> 00:00:52.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is that?

13
00:00:52.886 --> 00:00:54.554 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The eighth muscle pull
this month?

14
00:00:54.637 --> 00:00:58.975 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Actually, I believe
Commander Dax has been treated

15
00:00:59.059 --> 00:01:01.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for seven muscle pulls,

16
00:01:01.352 --> 00:01:03.563 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
two contusions, and
three cracked ribs.

17
00:01:03.646 --> 00:01:05.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The only person who’s spent
more time in the Infirmary

18
00:01:05.940 --> 00:01:09.611 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
over the past few weeks
is… Commander Worf.

19
00:01:09.694 --> 00:01:12.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Isn’t there any way the…
the two of you could, uh…

20
00:01:13.031 --> 00:01:14.991 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
uh, you know…

21
00:01:15.075 --> 00:01:16.284 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Make love?

22
00:01:16.367 --> 00:01:18.328 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Without injuring yourselves?

23
00:01:18.411 --> 00:01:21.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Interspecies romance
isn’t without its danger.

24
00:01:22.207 --> 00:01:23.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s part of the fun.

25
00:01:25.794 --> 00:01:27.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe we’ll have
better luck on Risa.

26
00:01:27.962 --> 00:01:29.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Risa?

27
00:01:29.297 --> 00:01:30.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought you and Worf

28
00:01:31.007 --> 00:01:32.509 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
were taking your
vacation on Earth.

29
00:01:32.592 --> 00:01:34.928 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That was his suggestion.

30
00:01:35.011 --> 00:01:36.554 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I changed his mind.

31
00:01:36.638 --> 00:01:38.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
ODO: From what I hear

32
00:01:38.223 --> 00:01:42.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Risa make the Hoobishan Baths
look like a monastery.

33
00:01:42.393 --> 00:01:44.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hope they have
a good hospital.

34
00:01:44.479 --> 00:01:45.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>chuckling </i>)

35
00:01:46.981 --> 00:01:48.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
SISKO:
I can’t believe

36
00:01:48.733 --> 00:01:51.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you actually convinced Worf
to go to a pleasure planet.

37
00:01:51.736 --> 00:01:54.155 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He must really be loosening up.

38
00:01:54.239 --> 00:01:56.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hadn’t noticed it.

39
00:01:56.950 --> 00:01:58.701 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come to think of it,
neither have I.

40
00:01:58.785 --> 00:02:01.204 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, no, he’s still
the same old Worf.

41
00:02:01.287 --> 00:02:02.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Prune juice, extra large.

42
00:02:02.789 --> 00:02:04.457 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
See what I mean?

43
00:02:05.708 --> 00:02:07.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Worf.

44
00:02:11.131 --> 00:02:13.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Captain, Constable…

45
00:02:13.716 --> 00:02:16.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander.

46
00:02:16.302 --> 00:02:19.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh, Dax said…
you were going to Risa.

47
00:02:19.389 --> 00:02:21.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did she?

48
00:02:22.433 --> 00:02:23.434 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, it’s no secret.

49
00:02:23.518 --> 00:02:25.645 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Apparently not.

50
00:02:25.728 --> 00:02:27.647 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You must be
looking forward to it.

51
00:02:27.730 --> 00:02:29.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m looking forward
to spending some time alone

52
00:02:29.691 --> 00:02:31.359 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
with Lieutenant Commander Dax.

53
00:02:31.442 --> 00:02:33.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Isn’t he sweet?

54
00:02:34.237 --> 00:02:36.197 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We have much to discuss.

55
00:02:36.281 --> 00:02:37.365 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
About what?

56
00:02:37.448 --> 00:02:39.284 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It is a private matter.

57
00:02:39.367 --> 00:02:40.285 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh.

58
00:02:40.368 --> 00:02:41.703 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
DAX:
Worf’s upset

59
00:02:41.786 --> 00:02:43.496 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because I had lunch
with Captain Boday.

60
00:02:43.580 --> 00:02:44.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Gallamite?

61
00:02:44.831 --> 00:02:47.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His skull is transparent.

62
00:02:47.167 --> 00:02:48.334 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And if you couldn’t see
his brains,

63
00:02:48.418 --> 00:02:49.919 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
would it make you
feel any better?

64
00:02:50.003 --> 00:02:51.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is not proper
for you to have lunch

65
00:02:51.671 --> 00:02:53.923 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
with an ex-lover
while we are together.

66
00:02:54.007 --> 00:02:56.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We were just talking.

67
00:02:56.509 --> 00:02:58.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You have to learn
to trust me a little more.

68
00:02:58.511 --> 00:03:00.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
WORF:
I do trust you.

69
00:03:00.346 --> 00:03:04.017 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I do not trust Captain Boday.

70
00:03:04.100 --> 00:03:06.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well…

71
00:03:06.185 --> 00:03:09.022 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can see it’s going to be
quite a trip.

72
00:03:10.523 --> 00:03:12.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, the two of you
have to tell us

73
00:03:12.525 --> 00:03:14.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
all about it
when you get back.

74
00:03:14.277 --> 00:03:16.237 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am sure <i>she </i>will.

75
00:03:20.491 --> 00:03:22.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I do not see why you
feel the need to talk

76
00:03:23.077 --> 00:03:25.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
about our personal lives
to other people.

77
00:03:25.538 --> 00:03:26.915 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I don’t see why
you feel the need

78
00:03:26.998 --> 00:03:28.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to control my every move.

79
00:03:28.917 --> 00:03:30.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And they’re not other people.

80
00:03:30.460 --> 00:03:33.421 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Benjamin and Odo are my friends.

81
00:03:33.504 --> 00:03:35.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
BASHIR:
Jadzia.

82
00:03:35.215 --> 00:03:36.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey.

83
00:03:36.216 --> 00:03:37.217 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Worf.

84
00:03:37.300 --> 00:03:38.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We’ve been looking for you.

85
00:03:38.676 --> 00:03:39.886 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Um, I’ve been thinking
about this trip

86
00:03:39.969 --> 00:03:41.179 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you’re taking
to Risa.

87
00:03:41.262 --> 00:03:42.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He’s a friend, too.

88
00:03:42.597 --> 00:03:44.057 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
LEETA: Julian and I
were talking it over,

89
00:03:44.140 --> 00:03:45.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and we’d like
to come along…

90
00:03:46.017 --> 00:03:47.143 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
if that’s all right.

91
00:03:48.394 --> 00:03:50.313 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Actually, we were hoping

92
00:03:50.396 --> 00:03:52.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to spend some time
alone together.

93
00:03:52.398 --> 00:03:53.858 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, you’ll have it.

94
00:03:53.942 --> 00:03:55.944 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, once we get to Risa,
you won’t even see us.

95
00:03:58.529 --> 00:04:00.949 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There’s no harm
in sharing a runabout.

96
00:04:03.034 --> 00:04:04.285 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I suppose not.

97
00:04:04.369 --> 00:04:06.120 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh!
Thank you so much!

98
00:04:06.204 --> 00:04:07.956 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m going
to go pack.

99
00:04:08.039 --> 00:04:09.290 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander…

100
00:04:09.374 --> 00:04:10.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do not hug me.

101
00:04:10.917 --> 00:04:13.169 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I promise we’ll keep
out of your hair.

102
00:04:13.253 --> 00:04:14.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good.

103
00:04:14.963 --> 00:04:18.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Because we have
much to discuss.

104
00:04:28.017 --> 00:04:30.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I really wish
I was going with you.

105
00:04:30.353 --> 00:04:33.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dax and I had
some great times on Risa.

106
00:04:33.481 --> 00:04:35.358 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>laughing </i>)

107
00:04:35.441 --> 00:04:37.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Curzon Dax.

108
00:04:37.318 --> 00:04:38.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Curzon.

109
00:04:38.987 --> 00:04:40.029 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course.

110
00:04:43.574 --> 00:04:44.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have fun.

111
00:04:49.831 --> 00:04:52.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s about time you got here.

112
00:04:52.166 --> 00:04:55.003 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The rest of us were ready
to leave an hour ago.

113
00:04:55.086 --> 00:04:56.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is he doing here?

114
00:04:57.046 --> 00:04:58.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ve always wanted
to go to Risa,

115
00:04:59.048 --> 00:05:00.383 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and this seemed like
a perfect opportunity.

116
00:05:00.466 --> 00:05:01.759 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He wouldn’t
give me any time off

117
00:05:01.843 --> 00:05:03.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
unless we promised
to take him with us.

118
00:05:03.344 --> 00:05:04.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hope this isn’t
going to be a problem.

119
00:05:04.887 --> 00:05:07.140 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
QUARK: Why should it
be a problem?

120
00:05:07.223 --> 00:05:08.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We’re going to have
a wonderful time.

121
00:05:08.891 --> 00:05:11.185 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, if you don’t mind,
Risa awaits.

122
00:05:13.062 --> 00:05:14.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry.

123
00:05:19.444 --> 00:05:20.820 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jadzia…

124
00:05:22.905 --> 00:05:24.449 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I know, I know.

125
00:05:24.532 --> 00:05:26.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We have much to discuss.

126
00:07:35.538 --> 00:07:39.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Let’s see… that’s
a Tarkalean tea for you,

127
00:07:39.584 --> 00:07:41.711 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a <i>raktajino </i>for you,

128
00:07:41.794 --> 00:07:43.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
and an extra large
prune juice.

129
00:07:43.713 --> 00:07:45.715 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Leeta, you’re on vacation,
not at Quark’s.

130
00:07:45.798 --> 00:07:47.008 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
You don’t have
to serve us.

131
00:07:47.091 --> 00:07:48.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Oh, it gives me
something to do.

132
00:07:48.551 --> 00:07:50.094 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Space travel’s so dull.

133
00:07:50.178 --> 00:07:52.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Have you ever noticed
how all stars look the same?

134
00:07:52.597 --> 00:07:55.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Excuse me…

135
00:07:55.099 --> 00:07:57.351 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
but I believe I ordered
a snail juice--

136
00:07:57.435 --> 00:07:58.352 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
hand-squeezed.

137
00:07:58.436 --> 00:07:59.479 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Get it yourself.

138
00:07:59.562 --> 00:08:00.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I’m on vacation.

139
00:08:00.771 --> 00:08:02.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
How much longer
till we get there?

140
00:08:02.815 --> 00:08:04.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
DAX:
Another six hours.

141
00:08:04.734 --> 00:08:06.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
QUARK:
Six hours?

142
00:08:06.319 --> 00:08:08.488 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Tell the Ferengi
to return to his cabin.

143
00:08:08.571 --> 00:08:10.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
You call that a cabin?

144
00:08:10.281 --> 00:08:12.658 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
It’s a cot
and a waste disposal unit.

145
00:08:12.742 --> 00:08:15.036 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
It’s so small
even I can’t stand up in there.

146
00:08:15.119 --> 00:08:17.246 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Look-- I’m developing a slouch.

147
00:08:17.330 --> 00:08:19.790 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Tell the Ferengi
to return to his cabin <i>now.</i>

148
00:08:19.874 --> 00:08:21.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Quark…

149
00:08:21.167 --> 00:08:22.293 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What’s he going to do?

150
00:08:22.376 --> 00:08:24.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Turn around
and take me home?

151
00:08:24.128 --> 00:08:25.046 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Ruin everyone’s vacation?

152
00:08:25.129 --> 00:08:26.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Coming about.

153
00:08:26.297 --> 00:08:27.548 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Setting course

154
00:08:27.632 --> 00:08:28.549 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
for Deep Space 9.

155
00:08:28.633 --> 00:08:30.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Okay, okay.

156
00:08:30.510 --> 00:08:32.011 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
You made your point.

157
00:08:32.094 --> 00:08:33.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I’m going.

158
00:08:33.721 --> 00:08:37.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
But first, I have
a little present for everyone.

159
00:08:37.642 --> 00:08:39.227 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
One for you.

160
00:08:39.310 --> 00:08:42.313 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
And one for you.

161
00:08:42.396 --> 00:08:45.608 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
And one for you.

162
00:08:45.691 --> 00:08:48.319 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
And none for you.

163
00:08:48.402 --> 00:08:49.445 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What’s this?

164
00:08:49.529 --> 00:08:50.738 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
It’s a <i>Horga’hn.</i>

165
00:08:50.821 --> 00:08:54.200 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
A Risian fertility symbol.

166
00:08:54.283 --> 00:08:55.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Displaying one
to the locals

167
00:08:55.743 --> 00:08:58.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
indicates you’re
seeking <i>jamaharon.</i>

168
00:08:58.871 --> 00:09:00.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
LEETA:
What’s <i>jamaharon?</i>

169
00:09:00.665 --> 00:09:04.335 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I’ll show you later.

170
00:09:04.418 --> 00:09:06.003 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Oh.

171
00:09:06.087 --> 00:09:08.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Look.

172
00:09:08.172 --> 00:09:10.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
They like each other.

173
00:09:10.883 --> 00:09:13.094 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think I’m going
to be sick.

174
00:09:13.177 --> 00:09:15.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>All right. </i>I’m going.

175
00:09:15.346 --> 00:09:17.265 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me, too.

176
00:09:19.350 --> 00:09:21.143 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Going? Where?

177
00:09:21.227 --> 00:09:23.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m going to change
into something more comfortable.

178
00:09:24.063 --> 00:09:25.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You don’t think
I’m going to beam down to Risa

179
00:09:25.856 --> 00:09:27.942 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
dressed like this, do you?

180
00:09:29.569 --> 00:09:30.611 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s a good idea.

181
00:09:35.032 --> 00:09:36.617 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
When in Rome…

182
00:09:38.703 --> 00:09:40.121 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

183
00:10:03.811 --> 00:10:05.479 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh!

184
00:10:05.563 --> 00:10:08.316 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can’t believe
we finally made it.

185
00:10:10.401 --> 00:10:13.070 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, enjoy your vacation.

186
00:10:13.154 --> 00:10:14.530 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mmm. We will.

187
00:10:14.614 --> 00:10:17.700 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Time to test
these babies out.

188
00:10:17.783 --> 00:10:20.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ladies…

189
00:10:22.496 --> 00:10:24.373 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You seek <i>jamaharon?</i>

190
00:10:24.457 --> 00:10:27.251 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I seek whatever you’ve got.

191
00:10:27.335 --> 00:10:29.545 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All that is ours
is yours.

192
00:10:34.258 --> 00:10:35.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ll take it.

193
00:10:39.138 --> 00:10:41.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Aren’t you uncomfortable
in that uniform?

194
00:10:41.432 --> 00:10:43.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Starfleet uniforms
are designed for comfort,

195
00:10:43.851 --> 00:10:46.687 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
even in the most
extreme environments.

196
00:10:46.771 --> 00:10:48.689 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, you look
out of place.

197
00:10:48.773 --> 00:10:50.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I mean, look around you.

198
00:10:50.608 --> 00:10:52.151 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Isn’t it beautiful?

199
00:10:52.234 --> 00:10:54.236 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is an artificially
created paradise,

200
00:10:54.320 --> 00:10:56.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
maintained by the most elaborate
weather control system

201
00:10:56.906 --> 00:10:58.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in the Federation.

202
00:10:58.449 --> 00:11:00.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In its natural state,
Risa is nothing more

203
00:11:00.743 --> 00:11:03.162 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
than a rain-soaked,
geologically unstable jungle.

204
00:11:03.245 --> 00:11:04.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe so,

205
00:11:04.789 --> 00:11:07.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but the only dark cloud
I see around here is <i>you.</i>

206
00:11:07.792 --> 00:11:10.044 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I did not come here
to admire the scenery.

207
00:11:10.127 --> 00:11:12.004 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you say so.

208
00:11:12.088 --> 00:11:14.006 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I guess we should
just go home.

209
00:11:14.090 --> 00:11:15.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, maybe…

210
00:11:18.594 --> 00:11:20.304 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I would not be so hasty.

211
00:11:20.388 --> 00:11:22.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I take it
the scenery has improved.

212
00:11:24.600 --> 00:11:26.060 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A few months ago

213
00:11:26.143 --> 00:11:27.686 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
when I was commanding
the <i>Defiant</i>

214
00:11:27.770 --> 00:11:29.563 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
on a scouting mission
in the Gamma Quadrant,

215
00:11:29.647 --> 00:11:31.649 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we encountered
a protostar cluster--

216
00:11:31.732 --> 00:11:33.359 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a swirling mass of color

217
00:11:33.442 --> 00:11:35.694 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
set against
a background

218
00:11:35.778 --> 00:11:38.239 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of glowing clouds
and burning sky.

219
00:11:38.322 --> 00:11:42.201 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It was the most beautiful thing
I’d ever seen…

220
00:11:42.284 --> 00:11:44.036 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
until now.

221
00:11:46.497 --> 00:11:49.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ve got to take you
on vacation more often.

222
00:11:51.794 --> 00:11:53.796 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dax, is that you?

223
00:11:55.047 --> 00:11:56.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Arandis.

224
00:11:56.340 --> 00:11:58.259 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was wondering
if you were still here.

225
00:11:58.342 --> 00:12:00.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh!

226
00:12:00.261 --> 00:12:02.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Not only am I still here,
I have been promoted.

227
00:12:02.763 --> 00:12:05.599 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m Chief Facilitator for
the entire Temtibi Lagoon.

228
00:12:05.683 --> 00:12:08.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Worf, this is Arandis.

229
00:12:08.477 --> 00:12:09.770 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A friend
of Curzon’s.

230
00:12:09.854 --> 00:12:11.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She and Curzon spent
a lot of time together

231
00:12:11.689 --> 00:12:13.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
on his last trip here.

232
00:12:13.691 --> 00:12:15.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We had a wonderful time
together…

233
00:12:15.818 --> 00:12:17.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
until I killed him.

234
00:12:17.278 --> 00:12:18.362 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Killed him?!

235
00:12:18.446 --> 00:12:21.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Death by <i>jamaharon.</i>

236
00:12:21.240 --> 00:12:23.492 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I suppose there
are worse ways to go.

237
00:12:23.576 --> 00:12:26.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Trust me, he died happy.

238
00:12:26.287 --> 00:12:28.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He was such a sweet old man.

239
00:12:28.747 --> 00:12:30.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I will take your word for it.

240
00:12:32.376 --> 00:12:34.003 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s so good
to see you again, Dax.

241
00:12:34.086 --> 00:12:36.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your new host
is very attractive.

242
00:12:36.464 --> 00:12:37.381 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you.

243
00:12:37.465 --> 00:12:38.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’d like to think so.

244
00:12:38.466 --> 00:12:40.050 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You haven’t aged
a day.

245
00:12:40.134 --> 00:12:42.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ah… Risa’s been
very kind to me.

246
00:12:42.511 --> 00:12:44.138 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come, let me
show you around.

247
00:12:44.221 --> 00:12:45.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe later.

248
00:12:47.433 --> 00:12:48.642 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course.

249
00:12:48.726 --> 00:12:50.603 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All that is ours is yours.

250
00:12:50.686 --> 00:12:51.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you.

251
00:12:51.896 --> 00:12:53.481 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But we have everything we need.

252
00:13:01.280 --> 00:13:03.532 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That wasn’t very nice.

253
00:13:03.616 --> 00:13:05.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why? Is there something
of hers you want?

254
00:13:06.076 --> 00:13:08.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Arandis was Curzon’s lover,
not mine.

255
00:13:09.079 --> 00:13:10.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hope you
remember that.

256
00:13:10.831 --> 00:13:13.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You’re still angry
about Captain Boday.

257
00:13:13.375 --> 00:13:15.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If I <i>am </i>angry, it is because

258
00:13:15.544 --> 00:13:18.339 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you do not take our
relationship seriously.

259
00:13:18.422 --> 00:13:19.548 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Worf, we just got here.

260
00:13:19.632 --> 00:13:21.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do we have
to start arguing again?

261
00:13:21.634 --> 00:13:25.262 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you were a Klingon woman,
we would already be married.

262
00:13:25.346 --> 00:13:27.765 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In case you haven’t noticed,
I am not a Klingon woman.

263
00:13:27.848 --> 00:13:29.725 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That is no excuse.

264
00:13:29.808 --> 00:13:32.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have been loyal to you,
and I expect you to be loyal

265
00:13:33.062 --> 00:13:34.355 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to me in return.

266
00:13:34.438 --> 00:13:36.023 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have been loyal to you,

267
00:13:36.106 --> 00:13:38.025 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I’m not going
to let you run my life.

268
00:13:38.108 --> 00:13:39.944 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m not trying to run your life.

269
00:13:40.027 --> 00:13:41.362 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then I’m going to go

270
00:13:41.445 --> 00:13:43.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and have a big glass
of icoberry juice.

271
00:13:43.614 --> 00:13:45.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That is a mistake.

272
00:13:45.282 --> 00:13:47.535 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You are allergic
to icoberry juice.

273
00:13:47.618 --> 00:13:49.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It makes your…

274
00:13:49.286 --> 00:13:50.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
spots itch.

275
00:13:50.788 --> 00:13:52.373 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I like the taste.

276
00:13:52.456 --> 00:13:56.043 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Fine. Have as much
icoberry juice as you like,

277
00:13:56.126 --> 00:13:57.711 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but it is still a mistake.

278
00:13:57.795 --> 00:14:00.005 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But it is my mistake
to make.

279
00:14:00.089 --> 00:14:02.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, why don’t you
go up to our room

280
00:14:02.633 --> 00:14:06.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and put on your bathing suit
so we can swim in the lagoon?

281
00:14:09.598 --> 00:14:10.975 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
As you wish.

282
00:14:14.061 --> 00:14:15.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>door chimes </i>)

283
00:14:16.063 --> 00:14:17.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Enter.

284
00:14:21.735 --> 00:14:23.153 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hope I’m not disturbing you,

285
00:14:23.237 --> 00:14:24.488 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lieutenant Commander.

286
00:14:24.572 --> 00:14:25.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My name is

287
00:14:25.573 --> 00:14:27.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Pascal Fullerton.

288
00:14:27.241 --> 00:14:29.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m the chairman of the
New Essentialists Movement.

289
00:14:29.201 --> 00:14:31.328 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m not familiar
with that organization.

290
00:14:31.412 --> 00:14:33.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We’re dedicated to restoring

291
00:14:33.205 --> 00:14:36.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the moral and cultural
traditions of the Federation.

292
00:14:36.166 --> 00:14:38.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is a statement
of our principles.

293
00:14:38.961 --> 00:14:40.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But if you would
like to hear more,

294
00:14:40.546 --> 00:14:42.715 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we’re holding a rally
later this afternoon.

295
00:14:42.798 --> 00:14:43.841 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On Risa?

296
00:14:43.924 --> 00:14:45.551 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What better place?

297
00:14:45.634 --> 00:14:48.053 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This world revels in the kind
of self-indulgence

298
00:14:48.137 --> 00:14:51.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that’s eroding the foundations
of Federation society.

299
00:14:51.765 --> 00:14:53.642 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We intend to shut it down.

300
00:15:05.779 --> 00:15:08.282 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I really wish you’d
stop reading that.

301
00:15:08.365 --> 00:15:11.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I would not dismiss
Fullerton so quickly.

302
00:15:11.118 --> 00:15:13.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
His analysis
of recent Federation history

303
00:15:13.412 --> 00:15:14.914 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is both insightful
and disturbing.

304
00:15:14.997 --> 00:15:16.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What’s really
disturbing

305
00:15:16.582 --> 00:15:18.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is that you’re still
wearing your uniform.

306
00:15:18.208 --> 00:15:21.295 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It would not hurt you
to read this.

307
00:15:23.505 --> 00:15:25.049 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
LEETA:
Mmm…

308
00:15:26.133 --> 00:15:27.635 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
mmm!

309
00:15:27.718 --> 00:15:30.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, the truth is

310
00:15:30.471 --> 00:15:32.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
not everyone can
be a dabo girl.

311
00:15:32.598 --> 00:15:34.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
First of all,

312
00:15:34.516 --> 00:15:36.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you have to be able
to wear the clothes,

313
00:15:36.518 --> 00:15:39.063 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and believe me,
that’s not easy.

314
00:15:39.146 --> 00:15:40.731 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have to be able

315
00:15:40.814 --> 00:15:43.609 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to calculate odds in
your head very quickly,

316
00:15:43.692 --> 00:15:45.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and most importantly,

317
00:15:45.319 --> 00:15:47.738 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you need a very
supple wrist…

318
00:15:47.821 --> 00:15:49.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
like this.

319
00:15:51.408 --> 00:15:53.202 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dabo.

320
00:15:53.285 --> 00:15:54.828 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
DAX: …the end of
the Federation

321
00:15:54.912 --> 00:15:56.497 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
since the day
it was founded.

322
00:15:56.580 --> 00:15:57.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Trust me. I know.

323
00:15:57.831 --> 00:15:58.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, hi!

324
00:15:58.999 --> 00:16:00.709 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Leeta, what a surprise.

325
00:16:00.793 --> 00:16:02.002 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Care to join us?

326
00:16:02.086 --> 00:16:03.796 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We were just about
to take a reyamilk soak.

327
00:16:03.879 --> 00:16:06.548 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe later.

328
00:16:06.632 --> 00:16:08.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Worf.

329
00:16:08.759 --> 00:16:10.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Worf.</i>

330
00:16:12.388 --> 00:16:15.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sigh of contentment </i>)

331
00:16:15.641 --> 00:16:18.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That was not Dr. Bashir.

332
00:16:18.644 --> 00:16:21.021 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s none of our business.

333
00:16:21.105 --> 00:16:23.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are you defending
her actions?

334
00:16:23.190 --> 00:16:24.566 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I am not
defending anything,

335
00:16:24.650 --> 00:16:26.568 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but it’s not my
business or yours.

336
00:16:26.652 --> 00:16:28.654 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, what do you
say we go sign out

337
00:16:28.737 --> 00:16:31.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a couple of floaters
and take in the sights?

338
00:16:31.198 --> 00:16:32.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I cannot.

339
00:16:32.408 --> 00:16:33.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Essentialists
are having a rally,

340
00:16:34.076 --> 00:16:35.494 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and I plan to attend.

341
00:16:35.577 --> 00:16:36.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
( <i>sighs </i>):
You’re kidding.

342
00:16:39.248 --> 00:16:40.749 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re not kidding.

343
00:16:50.509 --> 00:16:53.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don’t these people have
anything better to do?

344
00:16:53.846 --> 00:16:55.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Perhaps you
underestimate

345
00:16:55.597 --> 00:16:58.058 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the power of
Fullerton’s message.

346
00:16:58.142 --> 00:16:59.977 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The plot thickens.

347
00:17:01.645 --> 00:17:03.063 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you were worried

348
00:17:03.147 --> 00:17:05.065 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
about Julian.

349
00:17:06.483 --> 00:17:09.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why are he and Leeta
not together?

350
00:17:09.653 --> 00:17:12.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don’t know, but don’t
jump to conclusions.

351
00:17:12.573 --> 00:17:15.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m sure there’s
a reasonable explanation.

352
00:17:15.200 --> 00:17:18.037 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This place is
a bad influence on people.

353
00:17:18.120 --> 00:17:19.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
ARANDIS:
Here for the show?

354
00:17:19.872 --> 00:17:22.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I would not call it
a show.

355
00:17:22.374 --> 00:17:25.377 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Really? I find Mr. Fullerton
very entertaining.

356
00:17:25.461 --> 00:17:27.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He seems
pretty determined

357
00:17:27.379 --> 00:17:29.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to discourage people
from coming here.

358
00:17:29.965 --> 00:17:32.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Risa receives millions
of visitors every year.

359
00:17:32.176 --> 00:17:34.094 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And all of them leave happier
than when they’ve arrived.

360
00:17:34.178 --> 00:17:35.512 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don’t see how one man,

361
00:17:35.596 --> 00:17:37.431 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
no matter how determined,
can change that.

362
00:17:37.514 --> 00:17:40.267 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Kahless fought off an entire
army at Three Turn Bridge,

363
00:17:40.350 --> 00:17:42.019 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and <i>he </i>was only one man.

364
00:17:42.102 --> 00:17:43.353 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Fullerton and his
Essentialists

365
00:17:43.437 --> 00:17:44.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
have been here
for about a month,

366
00:17:44.897 --> 00:17:46.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and no matter
how many speeches he gives,

367
00:17:46.732 --> 00:17:50.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the water’s still warm,
and the wind still smells sweet.

368
00:17:50.819 --> 00:17:54.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But, if he’s enjoying himself,
who are we to discourage him?

369
00:17:56.158 --> 00:17:57.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>scattered applause </i>)

370
00:18:02.706 --> 00:18:04.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s right.

371
00:18:04.416 --> 00:18:06.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Take a good look.

372
00:18:06.293 --> 00:18:09.463 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can only imagine
what you must think of me--

373
00:18:09.546 --> 00:18:12.049 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a middle-aged,
ponderous academic,

374
00:18:12.132 --> 00:18:13.717 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
sweating under
the hot Risian suns,

375
00:18:13.801 --> 00:18:16.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
wasting his time
telling you things

376
00:18:16.428 --> 00:18:18.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you don’t want
to hear.

377
00:18:18.847 --> 00:18:22.267 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But you know what I see
when I look at you?

378
00:18:22.351 --> 00:18:23.977 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Children…

379
00:18:24.061 --> 00:18:27.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
pampered, spoiled children.

380
00:18:27.439 --> 00:18:30.400 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
For some reason, the
citizens of the Federation

381
00:18:30.484 --> 00:18:31.860 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
have come to believe

382
00:18:31.944 --> 00:18:33.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that they are entitled
to lives of ease….

383
00:18:33.695 --> 00:18:34.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I may be wrong,

384
00:18:34.988 --> 00:18:36.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but didn’t he
just insult us?

385
00:18:36.198 --> 00:18:37.449 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you want
something to eat,

386
00:18:37.533 --> 00:18:39.326 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you get it from
a replicator.

387
00:18:39.409 --> 00:18:43.163 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you want amusement,
you go to a holosuite,

388
00:18:43.247 --> 00:18:47.543 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and if you need protection,
you call for Starfleet.

389
00:18:47.626 --> 00:18:49.628 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But someday…

390
00:18:49.711 --> 00:18:51.463 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
someday soon,

391
00:18:51.547 --> 00:18:53.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you’re going to
have to learn

392
00:18:53.382 --> 00:18:54.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to take care
of yourselves,

393
00:18:55.008 --> 00:18:57.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because if <i>I </i>see you
as helpless children,

394
00:18:57.761 --> 00:19:00.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
then how do you think
the Borg see you?

395
00:19:00.264 --> 00:19:04.017 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Or the Romulans or the Klingons
or the Dominion?

396
00:19:04.101 --> 00:19:06.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
These empires look
at the Federation,

397
00:19:06.603 --> 00:19:08.689 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and they see a prize--

398
00:19:08.772 --> 00:19:11.608 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a prize that we have
forgotten how to protect,

399
00:19:11.692 --> 00:19:14.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and if we don’t change our ways,

400
00:19:14.194 --> 00:19:16.446 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
they’re going to take it
from us.

401
00:19:16.530 --> 00:19:19.950 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mr. Fullerton has quite
a flair for the dramatic.

402
00:19:20.033 --> 00:19:22.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Does he <i>really </i>believe that?

403
00:19:22.452 --> 00:19:23.537 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think he does.

404
00:19:23.620 --> 00:19:25.080 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
…and re-embrace

405
00:19:25.164 --> 00:19:26.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the kind of hard work

406
00:19:27.082 --> 00:19:30.002 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that built the Federation
in the first place.

407
00:19:30.085 --> 00:19:32.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Or we can lie here,
napping in the sun,

408
00:19:32.546 --> 00:19:34.590 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
until we wake up

409
00:19:34.673 --> 00:19:38.719 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
with Jem’Hadar guns
to our heads.

410
00:19:38.802 --> 00:19:42.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The choice is ours.

411
00:19:42.639 --> 00:19:45.225 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Heaven help us
if we make the wrong one.

412
00:19:49.229 --> 00:19:51.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
BASHIR: What <i>are </i>you
talking about?

413
00:19:51.481 --> 00:19:53.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come on, Worf, this sounds
like nonsense.

414
00:19:53.525 --> 00:19:54.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am merely observing

415
00:19:55.027 --> 00:19:56.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that the Klingons would
never have attacked

416
00:19:56.653 --> 00:19:58.989 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
had they not believed
the Federation vulnerable.

417
00:19:59.072 --> 00:20:00.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Even now, since
the changeling

418
00:20:00.699 --> 00:20:02.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
was discovered on the
Klingon High Council,

419
00:20:02.451 --> 00:20:04.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
most of my people
continue to call for war,

420
00:20:04.828 --> 00:20:07.080 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because they think
they can win.

421
00:20:07.164 --> 00:20:09.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
None of this has
anything to do with Risa.

422
00:20:09.625 --> 00:20:10.751 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You cannot be certain of that.

423
00:20:10.834 --> 00:20:12.377 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
DAX:
All I know is

424
00:20:12.461 --> 00:20:14.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ve spent lifetimes
defending the Federation,

425
00:20:14.630 --> 00:20:17.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I deserve a vacation
every now and then.

426
00:20:18.926 --> 00:20:19.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Julian?

427
00:20:21.136 --> 00:20:23.013 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, <i>there </i>you are.

428
00:20:23.096 --> 00:20:24.765 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am so glad we came here.

429
00:20:24.848 --> 00:20:27.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m having
the most wonderful time.

430
00:20:27.392 --> 00:20:29.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I told you this was
just what we needed.

431
00:20:29.186 --> 00:20:30.103 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mmm…

432
00:20:32.606 --> 00:20:34.024 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Something wrong?

433
00:20:34.107 --> 00:20:35.776 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s nothing.

434
00:20:35.859 --> 00:20:39.071 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You two dishonor each other
with your actions.

435
00:20:39.154 --> 00:20:41.490 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you know
what he’s talking about?

436
00:20:41.573 --> 00:20:46.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You mean… we didn’t tell you
why we came here?

437
00:20:47.704 --> 00:20:50.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We’re conducting
the Rite of Separation.

438
00:20:50.165 --> 00:20:51.959 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s an old Bajoran custom.

439
00:20:52.042 --> 00:20:53.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
When a couple separates,

440
00:20:53.835 --> 00:20:56.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
they spend several days
celebrating their parting.

441
00:20:56.296 --> 00:20:59.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s a way to remember
all the good times

442
00:20:59.383 --> 00:21:02.594 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and to seek out
new opportunities.

443
00:21:02.678 --> 00:21:05.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A very wise and ancient culture.

444
00:21:05.847 --> 00:21:07.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
LEETA:
You know, Julian,

445
00:21:07.641 --> 00:21:09.393 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don’t think

446
00:21:09.476 --> 00:21:12.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ve completely gotten you
out of my system yet.

447
00:21:12.229 --> 00:21:14.439 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know exactly
what you mean.

448
00:21:14.523 --> 00:21:16.316 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Excuse us.

449
00:21:16.400 --> 00:21:20.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Um, we have a few…
details to work out.

450
00:21:26.994 --> 00:21:28.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Terminating
a relationship

451
00:21:28.787 --> 00:21:30.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
should not be taken
so frivolously.

452
00:21:30.831 --> 00:21:32.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not every relationship

453
00:21:32.582 --> 00:21:34.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
has to end like
a Klingon opera.

454
00:21:34.584 --> 00:21:36.211 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, no, no.

455
00:21:36.295 --> 00:21:38.005 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just the ones that
are important.

456
00:21:38.088 --> 00:21:40.340 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>furniture breaking </i>)

457
00:21:43.135 --> 00:21:44.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stay where you are.

458
00:21:58.108 --> 00:21:59.443 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On three.

459
00:21:59.526 --> 00:22:01.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
One, two…

460
00:22:01.194 --> 00:22:02.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wait.

461
00:22:02.279 --> 00:22:03.697 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s enough.

462
00:22:05.449 --> 00:22:09.328 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well… I hope
we’ve proved our point.

463
00:22:11.538 --> 00:22:13.540 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The power cells
are empty.

464
00:22:13.623 --> 00:22:15.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have no intention
of harming anyone.

465
00:22:15.959 --> 00:22:18.211 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don’t understand.

466
00:22:18.295 --> 00:22:21.548 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You think you’re safe here
in this "paradise" of yours,

467
00:22:21.631 --> 00:22:23.091 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but you’re not.

468
00:22:23.175 --> 00:22:24.885 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What if we had been Jem’Hadar

469
00:22:24.968 --> 00:22:27.137 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
or Klingons
or Romulans.

470
00:22:27.220 --> 00:22:28.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hmm?

471
00:22:28.597 --> 00:22:30.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’d be dead now.

472
00:22:30.640 --> 00:22:33.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Even you-- Starfleet officers--

473
00:22:33.185 --> 00:22:36.063 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
were lulled into a false
sense of security.

474
00:22:36.146 --> 00:22:38.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you could be taken unaware,

475
00:22:38.565 --> 00:22:41.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
what chance
do the rest of us have?

476
00:22:41.568 --> 00:22:44.071 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The sad truth is

477
00:22:44.154 --> 00:22:47.074 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the galaxy is a hostile place.

478
00:22:47.157 --> 00:22:51.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Forget that, even for a moment,
and you risk losing <i>everything.</i>

479
00:22:52.037 --> 00:22:53.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just something
for you

480
00:22:53.914 --> 00:22:57.209 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to think about while you wait
for your desserts.

481
00:22:58.502 --> 00:22:59.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right.

482
00:23:00.045 --> 00:23:00.962 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on, demonstration’s over.

483
00:23:01.046 --> 00:23:02.255 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Move along, move along.

484
00:23:02.339 --> 00:23:04.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As a Starfleet officer,
I have the authority

485
00:23:04.800 --> 00:23:06.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to arrest you
for what you just did.

486
00:23:07.052 --> 00:23:08.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But that would be
a waste of time.

487
00:23:08.887 --> 00:23:10.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We both know the Risians
won’t prosecute.

488
00:23:10.847 --> 00:23:13.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They don’t have
the courage for it.

489
00:23:13.433 --> 00:23:15.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Believe me, I wish they did.

490
00:23:15.519 --> 00:23:16.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander Worf…

491
00:23:16.937 --> 00:23:20.273 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
what did you think of
our little demonstration?

492
00:23:20.357 --> 00:23:23.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I cannot condone
what you have done.

493
00:23:23.360 --> 00:23:24.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe not…

494
00:23:24.736 --> 00:23:26.863 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I do think
you understand it.

495
00:23:41.878 --> 00:23:43.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

496
00:23:48.510 --> 00:23:51.096 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don’t know about you,
but it’s past my bedtime.

497
00:23:53.140 --> 00:23:54.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We need to talk.

498
00:23:54.808 --> 00:23:57.227 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
About the Essentialists?

499
00:23:57.310 --> 00:23:59.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No. About us.

500
00:23:59.604 --> 00:24:03.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, I suppose you have another
list of things I’m doing wrong.

501
00:24:03.775 --> 00:24:06.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I did not say you were
doing anything wrong.

502
00:24:06.736 --> 00:24:08.029 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s just that…

503
00:24:08.113 --> 00:24:10.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
some of your behavior…

504
00:24:10.407 --> 00:24:11.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What about my behavior?

505
00:24:12.075 --> 00:24:14.494 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
At times, you are too impulsive.

506
00:24:14.578 --> 00:24:16.496 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You-you act without thinking.

507
00:24:16.580 --> 00:24:18.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You have no
self-control.

508
00:24:18.415 --> 00:24:20.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And you think
I need you to control me?

509
00:24:21.793 --> 00:24:25.255 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jadzia, you are my <i>par’machkai,</i>

510
00:24:25.338 --> 00:24:28.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and that means everything
you do reflects on me.

511
00:24:28.425 --> 00:24:30.385 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m sorry if I embarrass you.

512
00:24:30.468 --> 00:24:34.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I just need to know
that you take this relationship

513
00:24:34.472 --> 00:24:36.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
as seriously
as I do.

514
00:24:36.349 --> 00:24:38.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I just wish
you’d relax a little

515
00:24:38.852 --> 00:24:41.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and let yourself enjoy
what we have together.

516
00:24:45.775 --> 00:24:50.197 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Worf, I’m not going
to change who I am.

517
00:24:50.280 --> 00:24:52.449 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nor am I.

518
00:24:52.532 --> 00:24:55.535 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, at least we agree
on something.

519
00:24:58.163 --> 00:24:59.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

520
00:25:01.625 --> 00:25:03.543 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why don’t we go to bed?

521
00:25:03.627 --> 00:25:05.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You go.

522
00:25:05.462 --> 00:25:08.048 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I will be there shortly.

523
00:25:09.424 --> 00:25:10.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

524
00:25:13.553 --> 00:25:15.972 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

525
00:25:22.771 --> 00:25:24.564 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This place looks
a lot better

526
00:25:24.648 --> 00:25:26.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
than it did
last night.

527
00:25:26.316 --> 00:25:28.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I guess the Risians
aren’t as lethargic

528
00:25:28.485 --> 00:25:31.112 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
as the Essentialists would
like everyone to believe.

529
00:25:31.196 --> 00:25:33.907 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Essentialists are
wrong about many things.

530
00:25:33.990 --> 00:25:38.245 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What Mr. Fullerton could use
is a little <i>jamaharon.</i>

531
00:25:38.328 --> 00:25:39.621 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No…

532
00:25:39.704 --> 00:25:41.081 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a lot of <i>jamaharon.</i>

533
00:25:43.625 --> 00:25:47.170 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’d buy him a <i>Horga’hn </i>myself
if I thought he’d take it.

534
00:25:47.254 --> 00:25:50.090 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

535
00:25:50.173 --> 00:25:51.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It looks like
he’s not the only one

536
00:25:51.800 --> 00:25:53.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
that could use some cheering up.

537
00:25:53.343 --> 00:25:55.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ve had better vacations.

538
00:25:55.887 --> 00:25:57.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Better than Risa?

539
00:25:57.389 --> 00:25:59.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

540
00:25:59.808 --> 00:26:01.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ve never known a Klingon

541
00:26:01.726 --> 00:26:04.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who had a tougher time
enjoying himself.

542
00:26:04.604 --> 00:26:07.190 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That’s no reason for you
not to have a good time.

543
00:26:07.274 --> 00:26:10.318 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Risa is famous
for its diversions.

544
00:26:10.402 --> 00:26:13.488 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wish it were that simple.

545
00:26:13.571 --> 00:26:15.365 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It was for Curzon Dax.

546
00:26:15.448 --> 00:26:16.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah.

547
00:26:16.449 --> 00:26:17.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And I can tell

548
00:26:17.951 --> 00:26:20.328 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
there’s more
than a little Curzon in you.

549
00:26:20.412 --> 00:26:23.290 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He loved this planet.

550
00:26:23.373 --> 00:26:25.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And Risa loved him.

551
00:26:27.210 --> 00:26:29.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why don’t I help you clean up?

552
00:26:31.756 --> 00:26:33.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All that is ours is yours.

553
00:26:36.052 --> 00:26:38.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
LEETA:
Our paths have grown apart.

554
00:26:45.770 --> 00:26:48.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What was one is now two.

555
00:26:50.817 --> 00:26:54.571 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The time for sharing
is over.

556
00:26:59.868 --> 00:27:01.703 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
May the Prophets guide you

557
00:27:01.786 --> 00:27:03.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
toward the path of happiness.

558
00:27:03.830 --> 00:27:06.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And may they walk
with you always.

559
00:27:20.096 --> 00:27:21.348 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s it?

560
00:27:21.431 --> 00:27:22.891 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s it.

561
00:27:22.974 --> 00:27:24.351 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What were
you expecting?

562
00:27:24.434 --> 00:27:26.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was expecting
fireworks.

563
00:27:26.478 --> 00:27:27.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where’s the anger?

564
00:27:27.937 --> 00:27:29.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The vicious
name-calling?

565
00:27:29.856 --> 00:27:31.483 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The irrational
accusations?

566
00:27:31.566 --> 00:27:33.610 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I never would have agreed
to be a witness

567
00:27:33.693 --> 00:27:36.529 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if I’d known you were going
to be so <i>civil.</i>

568
00:27:36.613 --> 00:27:38.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s disgusting.

569
00:27:38.198 --> 00:27:40.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Personally, I think
it was admirable--

570
00:27:40.116 --> 00:27:42.160 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
no recriminations,
no hurt feelings.

571
00:27:42.243 --> 00:27:44.496 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don’t think I’ve
ever felt this good

572
00:27:44.579 --> 00:27:46.039 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
about the end
of a relationship.

573
00:27:46.122 --> 00:27:47.457 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I agree.

574
00:27:47.540 --> 00:27:50.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now I can finally be honest
about my feelings.

575
00:27:50.085 --> 00:27:52.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What… does
that mean?

576
00:27:52.462 --> 00:27:55.215 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s just…

577
00:27:55.298 --> 00:27:57.717 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in the past
few months,

578
00:27:57.801 --> 00:28:02.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ve been… thinking a lot
about another man.

579
00:28:02.347 --> 00:28:03.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ahh…

580
00:28:03.807 --> 00:28:05.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Let me get
this straight.

581
00:28:05.392 --> 00:28:07.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
While you were still
dating Julian here,

582
00:28:07.519 --> 00:28:09.979 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you were having fantasies
about someone else?

583
00:28:10.063 --> 00:28:11.940 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’d rather not discuss it now.

584
00:28:12.023 --> 00:28:13.400 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, no, no, no, no.
You brought it up.

585
00:28:13.483 --> 00:28:15.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You might as well
tell me who it is.

586
00:28:15.443 --> 00:28:16.778 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, do tell.

587
00:28:16.861 --> 00:28:18.113 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

588
00:28:18.196 --> 00:28:19.572 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s…

589
00:28:22.158 --> 00:28:24.077 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me?

590
00:28:24.160 --> 00:28:25.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Your brother…

591
00:28:26.037 --> 00:28:27.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Rom.

592
00:28:27.539 --> 00:28:29.582 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My brother Rom?

593
00:28:29.666 --> 00:28:31.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His brother Rom?

594
00:28:31.251 --> 00:28:33.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He’s so cute…

595
00:28:33.378 --> 00:28:35.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and very sexy.

596
00:28:35.505 --> 00:28:37.465 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Cute"?

597
00:28:37.549 --> 00:28:39.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Sexy"?

598
00:28:39.217 --> 00:28:40.969 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Rom?
-Rom?

599
00:28:42.178 --> 00:28:43.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Here.

600
00:28:43.513 --> 00:28:45.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You need this
more than I do.

601
00:29:00.196 --> 00:29:03.074 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
ARANDIS: Just close your eyes
and watch your body.

602
00:29:03.158 --> 00:29:06.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let all the tension drain away.

603
00:29:06.119 --> 00:29:08.371 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doesn’t the clay feel good?

604
00:29:08.455 --> 00:29:10.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wonderful.

605
00:29:10.290 --> 00:29:13.460 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now pour your emotions
into it.

606
00:29:13.543 --> 00:29:15.128 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Begin to mold it.

607
00:29:15.211 --> 00:29:17.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Feel the texture
in your hands.

608
00:29:17.380 --> 00:29:18.673 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I do.

609
00:29:18.757 --> 00:29:21.217 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I feel it.
I really do.

610
00:29:21.301 --> 00:29:23.803 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I knew you’d get it.

611
00:29:23.887 --> 00:29:25.722 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dax.

612
00:29:25.805 --> 00:29:27.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Worf!

613
00:29:31.352 --> 00:29:33.229 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Worf?

614
00:29:58.922 --> 00:30:00.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m tired of giving speeches.

615
00:30:01.007 --> 00:30:02.634 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s time we took action.

616
00:30:02.717 --> 00:30:05.136 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We’ve taken action--
the raid on the solarium.

617
00:30:05.220 --> 00:30:06.679 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’ll be forgotten
by tomorrow.

618
00:30:06.763 --> 00:30:08.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>door opens </i>)

619
00:30:09.933 --> 00:30:11.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. Worf?

620
00:30:15.855 --> 00:30:18.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You want to make
people leave Risa…

621
00:30:18.608 --> 00:30:20.693 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think I know a way.

622
00:30:29.369 --> 00:30:31.621 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I probably would have reacted
the same way Worf did.

623
00:30:31.704 --> 00:30:34.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I mean, I know Arandis is
Curzon’s lover, not yours

624
00:30:34.749 --> 00:30:37.335 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but if I’d walked in on the two
of you together, well…

625
00:30:37.418 --> 00:30:39.796 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
trying to figure you out
at any given time isn’t easy.

626
00:30:39.879 --> 00:30:41.130 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I like that
about her.

627
00:30:41.214 --> 00:30:42.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So do I.

628
00:30:42.882 --> 00:30:44.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s the reason why I
chased after her so long.

629
00:30:44.509 --> 00:30:46.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Would you two please

630
00:30:46.469 --> 00:30:48.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
stop talking about me
like I’m not here?

631
00:30:48.847 --> 00:30:51.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s also the reason why I
stopped chasing after her.

632
00:30:51.349 --> 00:30:52.767 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re too much work.

633
00:30:52.851 --> 00:30:55.019 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Worf </i>is the one
who’s too much work.

634
00:30:55.103 --> 00:30:57.939 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What you need is a Ferengi.

635
00:30:58.022 --> 00:30:59.274 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe,

636
00:30:59.357 --> 00:31:02.277 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but what I want is Worf.

637
00:31:02.360 --> 00:31:03.820 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why?

638
00:31:03.903 --> 00:31:08.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Because he has the courage
of a berserker cat,

639
00:31:08.241 --> 00:31:10.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and he has the heart of a poet.

640
00:31:10.994 --> 00:31:13.079 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And the brain
of a pigheaded idiot.

641
00:31:13.162 --> 00:31:15.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, sometimes.

642
00:31:16.457 --> 00:31:18.084 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jadzia.

643
00:31:18.167 --> 00:31:19.085 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Any luck?

644
00:31:19.168 --> 00:31:20.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m afraid not.

645
00:31:20.503 --> 00:31:21.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
None of the staff
can find him,

646
00:31:22.005 --> 00:31:23.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I’m sure
he’ll turn up.

647
00:31:23.506 --> 00:31:26.509 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, no sense
waiting around here for him.

648
00:31:26.593 --> 00:31:28.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I say we take some floaters
up into the hills

649
00:31:28.595 --> 00:31:31.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and go skinny-dipping
in the hot springs.

650
00:31:31.180 --> 00:31:32.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I never thought
I’d say this,

651
00:31:32.515 --> 00:31:33.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but I’m with Quark.

652
00:31:33.641 --> 00:31:35.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What was that?

653
00:31:35.727 --> 00:31:38.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Great. Just
what we needed.

654
00:31:38.187 --> 00:31:39.480 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought it wasn’t
supposed to rain

655
00:31:39.564 --> 00:31:40.481 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in this part of Risa.

656
00:31:40.565 --> 00:31:42.317 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s not.

657
00:31:42.400 --> 00:31:44.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Something must be wrong
with the weather grid.

658
00:31:44.652 --> 00:31:46.529 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>thunder rumbles </i>)

659
00:31:55.371 --> 00:31:57.457 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
May I have your
attention, please.

660
00:31:57.540 --> 00:31:59.751 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Obviously, the weather grid
is experiencing

661
00:31:59.834 --> 00:32:01.628 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
some type of malfunction,

662
00:32:01.711 --> 00:32:04.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I’m sure we’ll be able
to repair it soon.

663
00:32:04.505 --> 00:32:05.632 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No…

664
00:32:05.715 --> 00:32:07.258 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
you won’t.

665
00:32:07.342 --> 00:32:09.010 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You’re responsible
for this.

666
00:32:09.093 --> 00:32:11.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, I authorized it,
but it was not my idea.

667
00:32:11.679 --> 00:32:13.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It was mine.

668
00:32:13.473 --> 00:32:15.183 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you serious?

669
00:32:15.266 --> 00:32:17.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He’s serious.

670
00:32:17.393 --> 00:32:19.437 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Worf, what did you do,
build an uplink

671
00:32:19.520 --> 00:32:21.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so you could take control
of the weather grid?

672
00:32:21.940 --> 00:32:23.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The grid has been deactivated.

673
00:32:23.608 --> 00:32:26.027 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It will take three or four days
to restore the system

674
00:32:26.110 --> 00:32:27.528 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to normal operation.

675
00:32:27.612 --> 00:32:29.238 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
During that time,
the inhabitants of Risa

676
00:32:29.322 --> 00:32:31.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and their guests will experience

677
00:32:31.282 --> 00:32:33.326 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the planet’s
natural weather cycle.

678
00:32:33.409 --> 00:32:34.619 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And for most on Risa,

679
00:32:34.702 --> 00:32:36.496 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that means rain,
and plenty of it.

680
00:32:36.579 --> 00:32:38.915 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But why are you doing this?

681
00:32:38.998 --> 00:32:40.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Because Risa is an illusion

682
00:32:40.500 --> 00:32:42.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
created
by weather control systems,

683
00:32:42.961 --> 00:32:45.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
industrial replicators,
seismic regulators.

684
00:32:45.672 --> 00:32:48.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If the Federation
is going to survive,

685
00:32:48.508 --> 00:32:51.302 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we’re going to have to stop
wasting our time with toys

686
00:32:51.386 --> 00:32:53.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and get back to the essentials.

687
00:32:56.140 --> 00:32:58.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m beginning to think
there’s no hope for that man.

688
00:32:58.643 --> 00:33:00.103 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>thunder crashes </i>)

689
00:33:00.186 --> 00:33:02.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Or for you, either, Mr. Worf.

690
00:33:07.902 --> 00:33:09.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Commander,
with all due respect,

691
00:33:09.946 --> 00:33:11.990 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
are you out of your mind?

692
00:33:12.073 --> 00:33:14.492 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, I think you will find me
quite rational.

693
00:33:14.575 --> 00:33:16.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As rational
as Klingons get, anyway.

694
00:33:16.452 --> 00:33:17.578 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Worf, this
is wrong.

695
00:33:17.662 --> 00:33:19.414 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I disagree.

696
00:33:19.497 --> 00:33:22.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If Federation citizens cannot
handle a little bad weather,

697
00:33:22.917 --> 00:33:25.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
how will they handle
a Dominion invasion?

698
00:33:35.596 --> 00:33:37.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
( <i>thunder crashing,</i>
<i>wind whistling </i>)

699
00:33:40.977 --> 00:33:44.147 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have seen drier days
on Ferenginar

700
00:33:44.230 --> 00:33:48.109 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and we have 178
different words for rain.

701
00:33:48.192 --> 00:33:52.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Right now,
it’s <i>glemmoning </i>out there,

702
00:33:52.113 --> 00:33:53.197 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and that’s bad.

703
00:33:53.281 --> 00:33:55.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you’re so miserable,

704
00:33:55.283 --> 00:33:56.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
why don’t you take
your <i>Horga’hn</i>

705
00:33:56.659 --> 00:33:58.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and go find some company?

706
00:33:58.369 --> 00:34:01.372 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have you taken a good look
at the Risians lately?

707
00:34:01.456 --> 00:34:03.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They’re even more depressed
than the guests.

708
00:34:05.501 --> 00:34:08.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m trying to organize
a game of hoverball.

709
00:34:08.337 --> 00:34:09.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Would either of you
like to join us?

710
00:34:09.839 --> 00:34:10.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In the rain?

711
00:34:11.049 --> 00:34:13.259 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, on one of the indoor courts.

712
00:34:13.342 --> 00:34:14.969 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Indoor hoverball.

713
00:34:15.053 --> 00:34:17.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s just wrong.

714
00:34:17.388 --> 00:34:18.598 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ll play.

715
00:34:18.681 --> 00:34:21.100 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Good.
That makes one.

716
00:34:21.184 --> 00:34:22.226 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Having trouble

717
00:34:22.310 --> 00:34:23.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
keeping the guests happy?

718
00:34:23.811 --> 00:34:26.147 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ve never heard
so much complaining in my life.

719
00:34:26.230 --> 00:34:28.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nobody came here
to sit around in the rain.

720
00:34:28.483 --> 00:34:30.151 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s not just
the weather.

721
00:34:30.234 --> 00:34:33.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
People are starting
to complain about everything--

722
00:34:33.362 --> 00:34:35.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the rooms, the entertainment,
the food.

723
00:34:35.406 --> 00:34:37.617 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What’s wrong with the food?

724
00:34:37.700 --> 00:34:39.452 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nothing, as far as I can tell,

725
00:34:39.535 --> 00:34:42.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but the guests say
it just doesn’t taste right.

726
00:34:42.371 --> 00:34:43.915 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s the humidity.

727
00:34:43.998 --> 00:34:45.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It dampens the food,

728
00:34:45.166 --> 00:34:47.460 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
makes everything mushy.

729
00:34:47.543 --> 00:34:51.464 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Trust me. There’s no word
for "crisp" on Ferenginar.

730
00:34:51.547 --> 00:34:54.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe Mr. Fullerton
was right.

731
00:34:54.634 --> 00:34:57.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe we have forgotten
how to deal with adversity.

732
00:35:00.765 --> 00:35:03.226 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
According to our figures,
the guest population

733
00:35:03.309 --> 00:35:05.061 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
has declined by 30 percent
in the last three days.

734
00:35:05.144 --> 00:35:07.146 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And you can be sure
the guests that have stayed

735
00:35:07.230 --> 00:35:09.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
are taking what you
have to say seriously.

736
00:35:09.607 --> 00:35:10.817 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s a start.

737
00:35:10.900 --> 00:35:12.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
One that you can build on.

738
00:35:15.029 --> 00:35:16.155 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re leaving?

739
00:35:18.324 --> 00:35:20.785 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have had my fill of Risa.

740
00:35:20.868 --> 00:35:24.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mr. Worf, you’ve been
an inspiration to us all.

741
00:35:24.122 --> 00:35:25.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good luck.

742
00:35:25.665 --> 00:35:26.582 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you.

743
00:35:28.459 --> 00:35:31.587 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You still have the uplink
to the weather control grid?

744
00:35:31.671 --> 00:35:33.464 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Right here.

745
00:35:33.548 --> 00:35:37.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
By tomorrow, the weather grid
will be restored to normal,

746
00:35:37.426 --> 00:35:40.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and no one here will remember
this ever happened.

747
00:35:43.349 --> 00:35:46.060 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I intend to send a message

748
00:35:46.144 --> 00:35:48.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
they won’t forget.

749
00:35:58.322 --> 00:36:00.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You must be feeling
pretty good right now.

750
00:36:00.491 --> 00:36:03.411 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The weather’s terrible,
the guests are miserable,

751
00:36:03.494 --> 00:36:06.205 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and more and more people
are leaving Risa every day.

752
00:36:06.289 --> 00:36:08.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Their response only
proves my point.

753
00:36:08.875 --> 00:36:10.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I see.

754
00:36:10.960 --> 00:36:14.630 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ruin the vacations
of a few hundred thousand people

755
00:36:14.714 --> 00:36:17.717 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to bolster the moral fiber
of the Federation.

756
00:36:17.800 --> 00:36:21.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I do not expect <i>you</i>
to understand.

757
00:36:21.304 --> 00:36:23.806 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I understand…

758
00:36:23.890 --> 00:36:25.850 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
even better than you do.

759
00:36:25.933 --> 00:36:28.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What you did had nothing
to do with Risa

760
00:36:28.811 --> 00:36:33.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
or the Essentialists,
or even the Federation.

761
00:36:33.441 --> 00:36:36.319 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s about you and me.

762
00:36:39.488 --> 00:36:41.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You give yourself
far too much credit.

763
00:36:41.949 --> 00:36:43.242 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do I?

764
00:36:44.827 --> 00:36:48.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You think I’m irresponsible,
frivolous…

765
00:36:48.748 --> 00:36:50.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that I care more
about pleasure

766
00:36:50.750 --> 00:36:53.169 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
than I do commitment.

767
00:36:53.252 --> 00:36:57.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What do you think is going on
between me and Arandis?

768
00:36:57.173 --> 00:36:58.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You <i>know </i>what I think.

769
00:37:00.718 --> 00:37:02.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That’s right.
I do.

770
00:37:02.345 --> 00:37:03.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you know what?

771
00:37:03.804 --> 00:37:05.806 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re wrong.

772
00:37:05.890 --> 00:37:07.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did it occur to you

773
00:37:07.683 --> 00:37:09.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to ask me about it?

774
00:37:09.852 --> 00:37:13.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Or… trust, just a little?

775
00:37:13.856 --> 00:37:16.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A Klingon woman would not have
given me grounds for suspicion.

776
00:37:17.026 --> 00:37:18.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And how would you know?

777
00:37:18.903 --> 00:37:22.281 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Curzon spent more time
with Klingons than you ever did.

778
00:37:22.365 --> 00:37:25.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You may have lived
among my people,

779
00:37:25.701 --> 00:37:27.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but you are not a Klingon.

780
00:37:27.370 --> 00:37:28.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am.

781
00:37:28.412 --> 00:37:30.039 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe so,

782
00:37:30.122 --> 00:37:32.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but you’re not like
any Klingon I’ve ever met.

783
00:37:34.418 --> 00:37:37.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

784
00:37:37.463 --> 00:37:39.632 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What happened to you, Worf?

785
00:37:39.715 --> 00:37:43.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You’re a paragon
of Klingon honor and discipline,

786
00:37:43.594 --> 00:37:45.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but when it comes
to the Klingon

787
00:37:45.805 --> 00:37:48.057 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
passion for life,
the exuberance,

788
00:37:48.140 --> 00:37:50.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the enjoyment of the moment,

789
00:37:50.351 --> 00:37:53.562 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you are constantly
holding yourself back.

790
00:37:53.646 --> 00:37:55.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why?

791
00:37:55.439 --> 00:37:57.817 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That is not the issue here.

792
00:37:57.900 --> 00:37:58.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think it is.

793
00:38:02.780 --> 00:38:06.242 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I do not wish
to lose you, Jadzia.

794
00:38:06.325 --> 00:38:09.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then talk to me, <i>please.</i>

795
00:38:15.126 --> 00:38:16.711 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You know from the age of seven,

796
00:38:16.794 --> 00:38:19.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was raised by humans
on the farm world of Gault.

797
00:38:19.463 --> 00:38:22.008 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It was a sparsely
populated world,

798
00:38:22.091 --> 00:38:23.926 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
no more than 20,000 inhabitants.

799
00:38:25.803 --> 00:38:29.265 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It often seemed as though
everyone knew everybody else,

800
00:38:29.348 --> 00:38:30.599 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but one thing <i>was </i>for certain.

801
00:38:30.683 --> 00:38:32.018 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Everybody knew me.

802
00:38:32.101 --> 00:38:35.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was the Klingon child,
the uncontrollable one.

803
00:38:36.022 --> 00:38:37.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was the biggest,
the strongest,

804
00:38:37.940 --> 00:38:40.443 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the most fearless child
on the entire planet.

805
00:38:40.526 --> 00:38:43.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I fought hard, played hard,
did as I pleased.

806
00:38:43.696 --> 00:38:46.449 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What changed?

807
00:38:46.532 --> 00:38:51.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When I was 13, I was captain
of my school soccer team.

808
00:38:51.495 --> 00:38:56.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We had made the championships,
and I was determined to win.

809
00:38:56.375 --> 00:38:58.419 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Near the end of the second half
with the score tied,

810
00:38:58.502 --> 00:39:01.172 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
my team got
a corner kick.

811
00:39:01.255 --> 00:39:03.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The ball
sailed up high.

812
00:39:03.507 --> 00:39:06.635 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Both I and one of my opponents,
a human boy named Mikel,

813
00:39:06.719 --> 00:39:09.722 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
leapt up to head the ball.

814
00:39:09.805 --> 00:39:15.144 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He had position,
but I was determined to score.

815
00:39:15.227 --> 00:39:17.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I remember laughing
with excitement

816
00:39:18.022 --> 00:39:20.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
as I threw myself at him.

817
00:39:22.526 --> 00:39:24.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Go on.

818
00:39:25.946 --> 00:39:27.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighing </i>)

819
00:39:27.406 --> 00:39:28.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The next thing I knew,

820
00:39:28.699 --> 00:39:30.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the ball was sailing
into their goal.

821
00:39:30.826 --> 00:39:34.372 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I roared with triumph

822
00:39:34.455 --> 00:39:36.707 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and turned around to Mikel
to gloat,

823
00:39:36.791 --> 00:39:39.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
only to find him lying
in the grass bleeding.

824
00:39:39.877 --> 00:39:42.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our heads
had collided

825
00:39:42.338 --> 00:39:44.173 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
when we both went up
for the ball.

826
00:39:44.256 --> 00:39:46.300 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I had not felt the impact,

827
00:39:46.384 --> 00:39:49.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I had broken his neck,
and…

828
00:39:49.720 --> 00:39:51.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
he died the next day.

829
00:39:54.725 --> 00:39:56.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It was an accident.

830
00:39:56.477 --> 00:39:58.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which only makes it worse.

831
00:39:58.437 --> 00:40:02.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Compared to Klingons,
humans are fragile creatures.

832
00:40:02.817 --> 00:40:04.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I realized at that moment

833
00:40:05.069 --> 00:40:08.989 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to live among them,
I must practice restraint.

834
00:40:09.073 --> 00:40:11.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That must have been
difficult for you.

835
00:40:11.742 --> 00:40:13.494 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
At first.

836
00:40:13.577 --> 00:40:16.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In time, it became a part
of who I was--

837
00:40:16.372 --> 00:40:18.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
who… I am.

838
00:40:20.793 --> 00:40:23.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And you’re still afraid
that if you lose control…

839
00:40:27.425 --> 00:40:30.845 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Someone I care about
might get hurt.

840
00:40:33.931 --> 00:40:35.850 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That explains a lot…

841
00:40:37.726 --> 00:40:39.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but you have to realize

842
00:40:39.895 --> 00:40:42.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
there are some things
in life you can’t control,

843
00:40:42.606 --> 00:40:45.359 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and one of them is me.

844
00:40:45.443 --> 00:40:48.070 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But what you can do is trust me.

845
00:40:48.154 --> 00:40:51.365 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I care about
you, Worf,

846
00:40:51.449 --> 00:40:55.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I would never do
anything to hurt you.

847
00:40:55.119 --> 00:40:57.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nor would I do
anything to hurt you.

848
00:41:00.624 --> 00:41:02.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who knows?

849
00:41:02.793 --> 00:41:06.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I may have more self-control
than you give me credit for.

850
00:41:07.756 --> 00:41:09.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>objects clattering </i>)

851
00:41:09.592 --> 00:41:11.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That felt like
an earthquake.

852
00:41:11.886 --> 00:41:14.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>rumbling </i>)

853
00:41:14.305 --> 00:41:15.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So did that.

854
00:41:15.806 --> 00:41:17.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Essentialists.

855
00:41:19.560 --> 00:41:21.312 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You should see them all run.

856
00:41:21.395 --> 00:41:23.939 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think they finally realized
that the party’s over.

857
00:41:24.023 --> 00:41:25.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Increase the feedback

858
00:41:25.316 --> 00:41:26.567 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in the tectonic
stress regulators.

859
00:41:26.650 --> 00:41:27.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If I do, there won’t be

860
00:41:28.027 --> 00:41:29.945 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a building left standing
on this part of Risa.

861
00:41:31.572 --> 00:41:32.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It might be
a good idea

862
00:41:32.948 --> 00:41:34.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to head to
the spaceport.

863
00:41:36.076 --> 00:41:38.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Or at least get
out of this room.

864
00:41:40.456 --> 00:41:41.749 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Very well.

865
00:41:41.832 --> 00:41:44.460 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think our work
is done here.

866
00:41:44.543 --> 00:41:46.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
WORF:
The uplink--

867
00:41:46.128 --> 00:41:47.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
give it to me.

868
00:41:47.463 --> 00:41:49.048 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. Worf, I suggest

869
00:41:49.131 --> 00:41:51.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you all get off this planet
as soon as possible.

870
00:41:51.509 --> 00:41:53.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have no wish to see you

871
00:41:53.344 --> 00:41:54.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
or your
friends harmed.

872
00:41:54.345 --> 00:41:55.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Give us the uplink,

873
00:41:55.679 --> 00:41:57.431 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
or the only person
who will be harmed is you.

874
00:42:02.269 --> 00:42:04.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought you were
one of us.

875
00:42:04.188 --> 00:42:07.483 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Perhaps I was for a
time, but I believe

876
00:42:07.566 --> 00:42:09.777 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the Federation will survive
the Dominion, the Borg,

877
00:42:09.860 --> 00:42:11.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and people like you.

878
00:42:11.695 --> 00:42:12.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. Worf…

879
00:42:12.905 --> 00:42:14.490 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
if you walk out of here now,

880
00:42:14.573 --> 00:42:16.075 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you’ll be turning your back
on the Federation.

881
00:42:16.158 --> 00:42:17.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don’t you see?

882
00:42:17.493 --> 00:42:19.411 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Overindulgence,
lack of self-control--

883
00:42:19.495 --> 00:42:22.289 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
they’ll destroy
everything we hold dear,

884
00:42:22.373 --> 00:42:24.124 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and you will be responsible.

885
00:42:24.208 --> 00:42:25.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You say that we have to return

886
00:42:25.709 --> 00:42:27.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to traditional
Federation values.

887
00:42:27.211 --> 00:42:28.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, I agree,

888
00:42:28.337 --> 00:42:32.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but one of those
values is trust.

889
00:42:32.383 --> 00:42:37.096 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is essential that
we remember that.

890
00:42:37.179 --> 00:42:39.473 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don’t you walk away from <i>me.</i>

891
00:42:43.852 --> 00:42:46.689 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I will do as I please.

892
00:42:48.023 --> 00:42:49.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>groaning </i>)

893
00:42:53.571 --> 00:42:55.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am on vacation.

894
00:43:04.290 --> 00:43:07.585 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Figures-- the weather
improves the day we leave.

895
00:43:07.668 --> 00:43:10.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can’t wait
to get home.

896
00:43:10.296 --> 00:43:13.215 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Not that I didn’t
enjoy myself.

897
00:43:13.299 --> 00:43:15.551 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’d better
go find Bashir.

898
00:43:15.634 --> 00:43:17.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He brought a <i>Horga’hn</i>
down to breakfast,

899
00:43:17.511 --> 00:43:18.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and that’s the last
I saw of him.

900
00:43:21.015 --> 00:43:23.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hope the two of you
enjoyed Risa

901
00:43:23.434 --> 00:43:24.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and will come again.

902
00:43:24.893 --> 00:43:27.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I did not think that
I would be welcome.

903
00:43:27.688 --> 00:43:28.689 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, you still have

904
00:43:28.772 --> 00:43:30.441 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a lot to learn
about our people.

905
00:43:30.524 --> 00:43:34.486 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I never got a chance
to say good-bye to Curzon Dax.

906
00:43:34.570 --> 00:43:36.530 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And you’re not saying
good-bye to me either.

907
00:43:36.614 --> 00:43:37.740 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ll be back.

908
00:43:40.367 --> 00:43:42.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And Risa will be waiting.

909
00:43:45.998 --> 00:43:48.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So, what do we do now?

910
00:43:48.375 --> 00:43:51.712 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now we watch
the suns set.

911
00:43:51.795 --> 00:43:54.006 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have a better idea.

912
00:43:54.089 --> 00:43:56.300 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why don’t we go swimming?

913
00:43:56.383 --> 00:43:59.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I… didn’t bring
